<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>shelly provision on Shelly CLI</title><link>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/provision/</link><description>Recent content in shelly provision on Shelly CLI</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-US</language><atom:link href="https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/provision/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>shelly provision ble</title><link>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/provision/ble/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/provision/ble/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="shelly-provision-ble">shelly provision ble&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Provision a device via Bluetooth Low Energy&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="synopsis">Synopsis&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Provision a Shelly device using Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE).&lt;/p>
&lt;p>This command allows you to configure WiFi credentials and other settings
on a new device without connecting to its AP network first.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>BLE provisioning requires:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Bluetooth hardware support on your computer&lt;/li>
&lt;li>The device to be in BLE advertising mode (typically when unconfigured)&lt;/li>
&lt;li>The device&amp;rsquo;s BLE address (usually shown as ShellyXXX-YYYYYYYY)&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>Gen2+ devices support BLE provisioning. Gen1 devices do not have BLE capability.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>shelly provision bulk</title><link>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/provision/bulk/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/provision/bulk/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="shelly-provision-bulk">shelly provision bulk&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Bulk provision from config file&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="synopsis">Synopsis&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Provision multiple devices from a YAML configuration file.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The config file specifies WiFi credentials and device-specific settings.
Provisioning is performed in parallel for efficiency.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Config file format:
wifi:
ssid: &amp;ldquo;MyNetwork&amp;rdquo;
password: &amp;ldquo;secret&amp;rdquo;
devices:
- name: living-room
address: 192.168.1.100 # optional, uses registered device if omitted
device_name: &amp;ldquo;Living Room Light&amp;rdquo; # optional device name to set
- name: bedroom
wifi: # optional per-device WiFi override
ssid: &amp;ldquo;OtherNetwork&amp;rdquo;
password: &amp;ldquo;other-secret&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>shelly provision wifi</title><link>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/provision/wifi/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/provision/wifi/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="shelly-provision-wifi">shelly provision wifi&lt;/h2>
